    <engine-patches>
      <patch id="1" file="EvidenceSufficiencyNode.cs" loc="+89" backward-compat="verified">
        Adds `predicate: "in"` rule shape (membership check) alongside existing `minCount` + `requireNonEmpty` rule shapes. 3 new EvidenceSufficiencyRule properties (Predicate, Value, ReadFrom) + new Validate() arm + new EvaluatePredicate() helper + MaterializeValueArray + ReadPathValue helpers. Regression: 8 existing EvidenceSufficiencyNode tests pass; the minCount path used by predict-matter-cost@v1 is untouched.
      </patch>
      <patch id="2" file="PlaybookOrchestrationService.cs" loc="+80" backward-compat="verified">
        Adds branch-aware skip semantics. For each node's upstreams, if ANY upstream emitted a `selectedBranch` (EvidenceSufficiencyResult.SelectedBranch or ConditionResult.SelectedBranch), the current node is skipped UNLESS at least one branching upstream selected it (by name match). OR-semantics for multi-upstream nodes handled correctly via `branchingDepsSelectingThisNode` counter. New TryExtractSelectedBranch helper (~36 LOC) reads camelCase/PascalCase SelectedBranch via JsonElement. Avoids changes to ExecutionGraph + Deploy-Playbook.ps1 — simpler than the engine-gap-analysis.md design. Regression: 63 orchestration tests pass.
      </patch>
    </engine-patches>

    <quality-gates>
      <gate name="build">PASSED — dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ — 0 errors, 15 pre-existing warnings (none introduced by Wave C1)</gate>
      <gate name="tests">PASSED — 82 tests pass (11 new + 63 regression + 8 EvidenceSufficiency)</gate>
      <gate name="code-review">PASSED — 0 critical, 1 warning (W-1 ObservationEmitterNodeExecutor 5-param ctor; matches r1 IngestOrchestrator pattern, acceptable), 2 suggestions (S-1 + S-2; both project-convention-consistent)</gate>
      <gate name="adr-check">PASSED — 0 violations, 2 informational warnings (Zone A boundary follows established pattern from Wave B; deploy coordination flagged per bff-extensions §F.4)</gate>
