        <action>Owner creates 4 new sprk_analysisaction rows in Dataverse (INS-SANI=130, INS-L1C=0, INS-L2X=0, INS-OBSE=140) via /jps-action-create skill</action>
        <action>Owner runs Deploy-Playbook.ps1 -DefinitionFile src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/Playbooks/universal-ingest.playbook.json</action>
        <action>Owner runs smoke test against a fixture document — verifies 6 nodes execute end-to-end on sufficient path; checkLayer2Gate=insufficient correctly skips layer2Extract + groundingVerify (Gap #2 patch behavior)</action>
        <action>Owner records parity check vs r1 IngestOrchestrator on same fixture; differences must be documented + intentional (criteria 5)</action>
      </required-actions>
    </deferred-deploy>

    <downstream-impact>
      <wave id="C2" tasks="021">Wave C2 (021 — prompt migration to sprk_systemprompt) consumes the 4 NEW INS-* action rows: INS-SANI, INS-L1C, INS-L2X, INS-OBSE. Wave C2 also handles renaming existing 8 Wave B INS-* rows to @v1 suffix per design-a4 §10.</wave>
      <wave id="C3" tasks="022">Wave C3 (022 — IngestOrchestrator.cs retirement) can proceed after C1 deploys successfully + smoke parity established. Wave C3 deletes IngestOrchestrator.cs + IIngestOrchestrator.cs + Ingest namespace + r1 prompt loader (if not used elsewhere).</wave>
      <wave id="C4" tasks="023">Wave C4 (023 — IInsightsAi.RunIngestAsync rewire) consumes the universal-ingest@v1 playbook directly via PlaybookExecutionEngine.RunPlaybookAsync. Wave C4 also wires the Layer 1 observation emission (currently deferred per playbook §node 2 comment-emission — either as a post-LLM hook on AiAnalysisNodeExecutor or via a new emitL1Observation node).</wave>
      <wave id="C5" tasks="024">Wave C5 (024 — per-invocation parameterization) leverages the Parameters dict already wired through NodeExecutionContext (Wave C1 addition). C5 adds the typed InsightsIngestParameters record + per-tenant override surface.</wave>
    </downstream-impact>

    <open-followups>
      <followup priority="LOW" wave="C3-or-later">Refactor PlaybookOrchestrationService.cs (now 1380 lines, >2× critical threshold). Candidate split into partial classes: top-level + NodeExecution + ConfigJsonTemplating. NOT in Wave C1 scope per spec Risk-1.</followup>
      <followup priority="LOW" wave="C4">When IngestOrchestrator.cs is retired (Wave C3), reconsider ObservationEmitterNodeExecutor ctor count (currently 5 deps; matches r1 IngestOrchestrator's 11-dep pattern). May consolidate emit + upsert + mirror into a single pipeline service.</followup>
      <followup priority="LOW" wave="C4">Layer 1 observation emission (current code path: layer1Classify executor produces classification but does NOT yet emit the L1 observation). Wave C4 options: (a) extend AiAnalysisNodeExecutor with optional post-LLM hook configured in playbook JSON, OR (b) add a separate emitL1Observation node. Design-a5 §4 Node 2 deferred this decision to Wave C4 per implementor pain assessment.</followup>
      <followup priority="MEDIUM" wave="post-deploy">Add full end-to-end smoke test against a real fixture document on spaarke-bff-dev once deploy lands. Verify both sufficient + insufficient paths produce expected observations in spaarke-insights-index.</followup>
    </open-followups>

    <suggested-adr-amendments>
      <amendment status="OPTIONAL" target="ADR-030">
        Wave C1 surfaced a clean pattern for ADR-030 §F.1 inspection on AUTO-DISCOVERED INodeExecutor registrations (vs the existing §F.1 pattern for endpoint-handler injection). Suggest documenting the auto-discovery case in ADR-030: "When a service is consumed only via auto-discovery (e.g., INodeExecutor → NodeExecutorRegistry IEnumerable), unconditional registration is sufficient — no Null-Object needed because the discovery container is itself unconditionally registered." Wave C1's InsightsIngestModule.cs lines 78-89 is the canonical reference impl.
      </amendment>
      <amendment status="OPTIONAL" target="docs/architecture/INSIGHTS-ENGINE-ARCHITECTURE.md">
        Document the branch-aware skip semantics introduced by Gap #2 patch as a new "Branch semantics" subsection. Today's playbooks use `selectedBranch` field on EvidenceSufficiencyResult/ConditionResult; downstream nodes are now SKIPPED when none of their branching upstreams select them by name. This is a behavioral change from r1 (where downstream nodes always executed after any successful upstream).
      </amendment>
    </suggested-adr-amendments>
  </notes>
</task>
